​Our Motto is Our Mission: Healing Thru Hockey.
We are more than a team; we are a force for recovery.

​The Warriors were founded on a simple, profound belief: the ice is a powerful place to heal. For many veterans, life has dealt a tough hand. From the challenges of mental health to physical injuries and trauma. We use the game of hockey not just for competition, but as a critical tool for rehabilitation, community, and purpose.
​We offer a supportive, non-judgmental environment where every player regardless of skill, experience, or background can lace up and find strength, camaraderie, and a new sense of identity.  ​

Our ability to provide these essential therapy, equipment, and ice time relies completely on the generosity of our community. When you support The Warriors, you are directly investing in a veteran's path to wellness. Help us keep the healing going by clicking the link below.

pages.title: About | Pittsburgh Warriors
h1s: Mission Pittsburgh Warriors Hockey is a 501(c)(3) organization of honorably discharged service members with a service-connected disability united around hockey and dedicated to provide a cathartic experience, promote physical and mental healing and growth as well as to enable team members to be even more productive members of society. Vision  Pittsburgh Warriors Ho ckey, with the help of the community, will use the powerful sport of hockey as a catalyst to create a culture of healing for its members in perpetuity. culture  Our time together will promote healing and we will help each other. There is no requirement for experience or ability to play. Pittsburgh Warriors Hockey can help shape a positive public perception of all veterans, and, because we also wear the Pittsburgh Penguins logo on our jerseys, we will strive to be examples of excellence in sport and community. Similar to our military service, we will promote brotherhood and camaraderie, seek to build friendships on and off the ice and foster a true team experience in our quest for victory. Recognizing the growing number of veterans dealing with substance abuse problems, depression, post-traumatic stress, and other unseen scars, excessive drinking will be discouraged. Unprofessional, inappropriate and/or illegal behavior will not be tolerated. required items  VA Rating letter, USA Hockey Number and DD-214

No previous ice hockey experience required
1.  Winning on the ice is important, but there is so much more.

2.  To promote brotherhood, each new player will be given a formal introduction at their first practice by the Head Coach or Assistant Coach. Additionally, at the beginning of every practice, one member will be asked to give a brief story or “fun-fact” about themselves that the others may not know.
3.  One’s ability has nothing to do with how you are seen as a teammate, everyone will play.
4.  While on the ice, only the Captain or Alternate Captains will talk to the referee.

View Past DVHL Champions About the DVHL The Pittsburgh Warriors Disabled Veterans Hockey League (DVHL) is an internal recreational league designed specifically for honorably discharged veterans with service-connected disabilities. Operating under the motto "Healing Thru Hockey," the league provides a safe and supportive environment where veterans can rebuild camaraderie, focus on mental and physical rehabilitation, and rediscover a sense of purpose. The DVHL is open to all skill levels from absolute beginners to experienced players and utilizes a "salary cap" draft system based on skill evaluations to ensure every team is balanced and competitive. More than just a sports league, it serves as a vital community where veterans support one another, with the organization providing all necessary equipment and training to ensure that no veteran is left behind due to a lack of experience or gear.
